This paper is about using deep neural networks for speech recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of highway networks, which is a technique for training deep neural networks, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on reducing the number of model parameters for resource-constrained platforms, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, since the paper is about neural networks, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
